Content:
Oh, and I just tested this on play.golang.org, and I had wrong results because <i>a</i> was too small, so we need to manually set it to an uint64:<p><pre><code>  package main

  import (
    &quot;log&quot;
  )

  func main() {
    max := 1000000

    var maxa int
    var maxlength int
    for a0 := 0; a0 < max; a0++ {

      var length int
      a := uint64(a0)

      for a > 1 {
        if a%2 == 0 {
          a = a/2
        } else {
          a = (3 * a + 1) / 2
        }
        length++
      }

      if length > maxlength {
        maxa = a0
        maxlength = length
      }
    }
    log.Println(maxlength, maxa)

  }
</code></pre>
Even more interestingly, this is even faster:<p><pre><code>  > time ./collatz
  2013/12/01 13:59:06 329 837799
  ./collatz  0,27s user 0,00s system 99% cpu 0,276 total</code></pre>
